    <article>
        <articleInfo lang="EN" FirstPage="80" LastPage="96">
            <pdf>26103-jdecp-korzyuk.pdf</pdf>
            <abstract>We consider the Cauchy problem for a mildly quasilinear wave equation with a variable coefficient in the upper half-plane. We use the method of characteristics to construct the solution in an implicit analytical form as a solution of an integro-differential equation. We study the solvability of this equation, as well as the dependence on the initial data and the smoothness of its solutions. We prove the uniqueness of the solution for the problem in question and establish the conditions under which its classical solution exists.</abstract>
            <title>Classical Solution of the Cauchy Problem for a Mildly Quasilinear Wave Equation with a Variable Coefficient</title>
            <keywords>
                <word>apriori estimates</word>
                <word>Cauchy problem</word>
                <word>classical solution</word>
                <word>mildly quasilinear wave equation</word>
                <word>parameter continuation method</word>
            </keywords>
